3\cdot 3 +3(3+3) - 3^3 &= 3\cdot 3 +3(6) - 3^3\\
&= 3\cdot 3 + 3(6) - 27\\
&= 9 + 18 - 27 = \boxed{0}.
\end{align*}

Simplify according to the order of operations. \begin{align*}
3!(2^3+\sqrt{9})\div 2 &= 6(8+3)\div 2 \\
&=6(11)\div 2 \\
&=66\div 2\\
&=\boxed{33}.
